<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870126-0145 </DOCNO><HL> Consolidated Natural GasPlans to Buy USX Unit</HL><DD> 01/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CNG XTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Consolidated Natural Gas Co. said it signed a letter of intent to buy USX Corp.'s wholly owned Apollo Gas Co. unit. Terms weren't disclosed.    The agreement is subject to execution of a final sales agreement and approval by both companies' boards, the Pennsylvania Public Utility Commission and the Securities and Exchange Commission.    Apollo's revenue in 1986 totaled $11.7 million. Consolidated Natural Gas is a natural gas and oil explorer and producer. </TEXT></DOC>